      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">20/11/95 ¶  ¶ Among the plants, kindly sent by you for the Field Naturalists floral Exhibition, dear Miss Henley, were also specimens of the Swainsona, ¶  of which I send you herewith a specimen back....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.11.20</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Maria Henley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M32a, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">20/11/95</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Among the plants, kindly sent by you for the Field Naturalists floral Exhibition, dear Miss Henley, were also specimens of the <name key="Swainsona">Swainsona</name>,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The file contains one of M's museum labels, undated, marked by M: '<name key="Swainsona">Swainsona</name> Near the Ovens River 1895 Miss Henley'. A further label, likewise undated, is annotated by M: 'Where do you get your excellent dark ink?.</p>
               </note> of which I send you herewith a specimen back. It cannot be safely named as species, until the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ripe fruit</hi>
               </seg> shall have been obtained. As the plant may not be rare near you, I would ask, whether you could send some <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fruiting</hi>
               </seg> specimens and also a lot of separate well ripened seedvessels with seeds, should this be easy for you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On the afternoon, when I met your worthy parents<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Henley, 18 October 1895 (in this edition as 95-10-18a).</p>
               </note> I had an opportunity of speaking to the young Italian Prince<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Luigi, Duke of the Abruzzi (1873-1933), who visited Melbourne in late 1895. His father, Amedeo, second son of King Vittorio Emanuele II of Italy and1st Duke of Aosta, was briefly King Amadeo I of Spain, 1870-3, but then abdicated.</p>
               </note> and I met his Royal Highness also subsequently in the Governor's palace and an other conversation. His father was when he was born King Amadeus of Spain, and as such he honored me with the Commander-Order of Isabella of Spain.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Amadeo I, King of Spain, to M, 8 March 1872.</p>
               </note> In acknowledgment I named a large Lake in honor of his Majesty.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lake Amadeus, NT, named at M's request by Ernest Giles.</p>
               </note> You will find it on any general map of Australia (Central region)</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If you find more of your <name key="Cordyceps%20Henleyi">Cordyceps Henleyi</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cordyceps Henleyae</seg>? Described by Massee (1895), pp. 28-9, from a specimen collected by 'Miss M. Henley' and communicated by 'Sir Ferd. Mueller'.</p>
               </note> kindly send the specimens</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You may see in your vicinity still other species of Cordyceps growing from dead insects, but they would likely smaller<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'be' omitted?</p>
               </note> kinds. Indeed other <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">rare</hi>
               </seg> fungs may be noticed by you there. If so, kindly secure some specimens of each uncommon sort and dry them before sending, and should the color fade, give a short note on the fresh color with each such species. You will in all instances get full credit for any discoveries of yours.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Do you require any particular seeds from here for your garden?<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You may see … garden <seg style="font-style: italic; ">is on a separate sheet. The reference to </seg>Cordyceps<seg style="font-style: italic; "> suggests it belongs to this letter</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cordyceps%20Henleyi">Cordyceps Henleyi</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Swainsona">Swainsona</name>
            </p>
         </div>
